description: From Middle English dethful, equivalent to death +‎ -ful.

adjectives.description: deathful (comparative more deathful, superlative most deathful)

entries.meaning: Involving the danger of death; fatal, deadly. [from 13th c.]
examples: Five hapless swains with soft allusive smiles / The harlot meshes in her deathful toils  […] .

entries.meaning: Resembling or pertaining to death; deathly. [from 15th c.]
